attributes.title: Tiring Day
attributes.caption: We're both wrecked and showing it.

attributes.title: Mind the Gap
attributes.caption: More offwidth. This last section wasn't too bad. The tree down below was a very welcome end to what was perhaps the crux of the climb in terms of chimneys.

attributes.title: Snack Time
attributes.caption: This must have been at the top of pitch four. The sun was out and full force and we were both really feeling it. But the belay station was set up between this tall flat rock  (behind me in the photo), and a tree providing the only shade we'd see for the next couple of hours. Great break spot.

attributes.title: Escargot
attributes.caption: I haven't eaten a lot of this stuff in my life, but, with all of that butter and pesto there's no way it wouldn't taste good.

attributes.title: Pitch 11
attributes.caption: These smiles were actually fairly forced. We were both beat.

attributes.title: Feet dyed red
attributes.caption: It's known that climbing shoes will discolor sweaty feet, but these looked pretty ridiculous. I guess that's what happens when you're in shoes all day.

attributes.title: Feet and Mountains
attributes.caption: The Sout of France was beautiful in ways I had not anticipated.

attributes.title: Our Chalet
attributes.caption: We spent a few nights here, great place.

attributes.title: Swimming
attributes.caption: You could plop in and float down 50m in no time at all.

attributes.title: Blue Water Under the Bridge
attributes.caption: Water was moving fast and quite cold. I checked.

attributes.title: Cragging
attributes.caption: On the right hand side of this photo is the crag. Literally the shortest approach of my life.

attributes.title: Tunnel Entrance
attributes.caption: You spend probably about fifteen minutes in tunnels on the approach to the climb.

attributes.title: Looking up at Le Demande
attributes.caption: We walked just a little past the approach to look at the wall. If you look, over towards the left there's a crack that trends up and left, then stops about half way. That's our climb. It's hard to believe it's 320m from this angle.

attributes.title: Gorge from the Start
attributes.caption: Good place to get all geared up!

attributes.title: Pitch 1 of Le Demande
attributes.caption: If you're wondering where to start the route, take a good look at this photo just to be sure. This is the spot.

attributes.title: Phil Traverses Pitch 2
attributes.caption: Fun little pitch that went pretty quickly.

attributes.title: Phil Leads Pitch 3
attributes.caption: Seemed like kind of a tough one, but not too bad. I spent a lot of time here waiting since Phil climbed past his planned anchor. Communication was tough and we almost had a dangerous mix up with "take", sounding too much like "safe".

attributes.title: Both Walls
attributes.caption: In the gorge!

attributes.title: Phil's Ambition
attributes.caption: Phil overshot the anchor on pitch three, which was actually pretty easy to do. He was also a bit low on gear and decided to make a belay station right where he was.

attributes.title: Across the Gorge
attributes.caption: Even more limestone on the other side.

attributes.title: River Below
attributes.caption: Just more glorious scenery.

attributes.title: Phil Pulling
attributes.caption: This pitch, I forget which, maybe 4 or 5, was actually quite a challenge. The crack didn't want to give me great hand holds a few times.

attributes.title: Dihedral to Face
attributes.caption: This bit moves out of the crack where phil is and across the face. The last moves felt very run out, and weren't especially easy. But it was nice getting out of the crack for some fresh air.

attributes.title: Demande Descent
attributes.caption: Just beginning the walk off.

attributes.title: From the Top
attributes.caption: This is after finishing Le Demande on the walk back down. You can't actually see our line from here, but it's not far from there.

attributes.title: Just off the road
attributes.caption: A place to get a 'snack' and pee. It was situated in a really beautiful place, just off the highway. They really do rest stops well in France.

attributes.title: Mini Sandwiches
attributes.caption: I don't think this is a normal French thing, but we got to try a bunch of sandwiches all the same.

attributes.title: Old car old homes
attributes.caption: It may have been too hot for a convertible this particular day.

attributes.title: Swallow Nests
attributes.caption: Spotted walking through a tunnel.

attributes.title: Continental Breakfast
attributes.caption: So many dishes!

attributes.title: Cragging
attributes.caption: This crag was actually a lot of fun. Very compact, but hundreds of climbs.

attributes.title: Courtyard
attributes.caption: The courtyard of our very pleasant BnB.

attributes.title: Phil pot Cragging
attributes.caption: Half in climbing mode, half in sandal mode, and feeling good.

attributes.title: My Bed
attributes.caption: Not a bad spot to spend a few nights.

attributes.title: Fields Outside
attributes.caption: Just near the house was a rather scenic bit of farmland.

attributes.title: Bridge over Green Water
attributes.caption: Found myself here a couple of times on a wander through the town.

attributes.title: Solstice Party
attributes.caption: A band playing Pixies and Alanis Morissette covers.

attributes.title: Eiffel Tower from the Bus
attributes.caption: Rolled past it, this was the only photo I got. Pretty cool structure!

attributes.title: A Bridge
attributes.caption: Just saw it on a walk, thought it was pretty.

attributes.title: Laura
attributes.caption: My friend Laura, who I know from high school.

attributes.title: Eiffel is an Eye Full
attributes.caption: At night, every hour they set off a light display on the tower. Really quite spectacular.

attributes.title: Sailing
attributes.caption: During a picnic we sat and watched a few older gentlemen walk back and forth with their RC sailboats. All wind powered, except for the rudder.

attributes.title: Eduard
attributes.caption: Got to catch up with Ed at his house for a few hours.

attributes.title: The Hood
attributes.caption: This is near where I spent a fair amount of time. I love the little red ghost.

attributes.title: Julia
attributes.caption: Julia, relaxing after a long day at the office.

attributes.title: Parisian Canal
attributes.caption: I love cities with canals.

attributes.title: Notre Dame
attributes.caption: I never knew what it looked like. It's really a very pretty cathedral.

attributes.title: Security at Notre Dame
attributes.caption: I was only slightly surprised to see these guys with automatic weapons walking around. I suppose everyone is on edge.

attributes.title: Notre Dame in the Distance
attributes.caption: I thought this was quite a nice vantage point of the cathederal.

attributes.title: Things Get Spicy
attributes.caption: Right at the to here is where things start to get tough, and it earns it's 7a.

attributes.title: More Ruins
attributes.caption: So many ruins. Rest assured there were tourists all around me when I took this photo.

attributes.title: Parthenon up Close
attributes.caption: It's cool, no doubt.

attributes.title: Sheila and Cory
attributes.caption: Got some other tourists to take a photo of us.

attributes.title: Strange Plant
attributes.caption: I'm not certain, but I thiknk, that this massive tree-like stalk is actually the flower of the plant. Talk about sexual selection.

attributes.title: Two Pups
attributes.caption: Two really sweet dog that belonged to our hosts.

attributes.title: Chilling on the Ferry
attributes.caption: A German couple was nice enough to snap our pic on the boat.

attributes.title: Monastary hike out
attributes.caption: On our way back from Monastary for some cragging, we witnissed our first Kalymnos sunset.

attributes.title: Post Climb Sapped
attributes.caption: We were both pretty beat, and we cracked a bottle of wine we were told was made from sap. It wasn't too bad.

attributes.title: Seaphordite View
attributes.caption: The view from the back of the house before it's too dark.

attributes.title: Everything is a Rest on this Climb
attributes.caption: Quest snapped this pic of me, it came out pretty cool.

attributes.title: Ruins
attributes.caption: Just encountered these on a walk.

attributes.title: Cityscape
attributes.caption: This distant hill has a church on it. Bookmarked to walk up that later.

attributes.title: Reading in the Garden
attributes.caption: I sat and read a book for a while just here. It's a nice little park to hang out in.

attributes.title: A Common Park
attributes.caption: Off the tourist track.

attributes.title: Rooftop Pano
attributes.caption: Thi is a panorama of the roof of our AirBnb rental in Greece. This place was really incredible.

attributes.title: Packed Parthenon
attributes.caption: This is the foot traffic during the low season. Crazy.

attributes.title: Sheila and the Parthanon
attributes.caption: This was on our way out of tourist hell.

attributes.title: A Place to Work
attributes.caption: The wifi wasn't great outside, but I did manage to get little bits of work done here and there.

attributes.title: Sunset over Athens
attributes.caption: A sea of houses, man of which are white.

attributes.title: Tourism on Mount Lycabettus
attributes.caption: We weren't the only ones with this idea, and it was a good one!

attributes.title: Parthanon at Night
attributes.caption: You can jut barely see it lit up at night in this photo. Honestly, this is one of the better places to see the Parthanon. It's not impressive at all in the photo, but you could make out much more detail and appreciate its scale in person.

attributes.title: Chicken Salad
attributes.caption: Way too much salad.

attributes.title: Kalymnos from Above
attributes.caption: I saw a landmass out the window of the plane and realized it was likely Kalymnos! Sure enough, I checked the map and it was. Though our plane was bound for Rhodes, it still got me amped to climb, just seeing the island.

attributes.title: Rhodes Castle
attributes.caption: The castle was really quite magnificent. You just have to avoid a bunch of the people trying to sell you things.

attributes.title: Dry Moat
attributes.caption: We finished our tour of the castle by walking around it. It's astonishingly huge. It took us ages to get back and find food.

attributes.title: Cat on the Wall
attributes.caption: There are cats everywhere, the moat can't even keep them out.

attributes.title: Poppies
attributes.caption: These impossibly red flowers were all over the place.

attributes.title: White Wine
attributes.caption: We were gifted a bottle of wine by our hosts. So lovely, and great for a hot day.

attributes.title: A Light Lunch
attributes.caption: I decided to get the larger gyro feeling quite hungry. I had no idea it was going to be the size of my head.

attributes.title: Sheila Rope Wrangling
attributes.caption: Sheila's first time coiling rope, it only gets easier from here.

attributes.title: Monastary Panorama
attributes.caption: Can't see anyone in any direction.

attributes.title: Goaty McGoat Face
attributes.caption: This goat seems to hang around the Grande Grotto area. She's absolutely a sweetie, and even likes to get pets. Just don't piss her off, she will head butt you.

attributes.title: Grande Grotto Kalymnos
attributes.caption: This cave is located just up behind Masouri. The walk isn't too bad, and the climbing is fantastic. Wonderful classic climbs can be found here.

attributes.title: Too Much Food
attributes.caption: Once again, we ordered way too much food. We continued to do this to ourselves somehow.

attributes.title: Sunset at Seaphrodite
attributes.caption: This sunset was snapped from our place in Panormos.

attributes.title: Seacliff
attributes.caption: Up at a climbing areah, but looking down at another. There's great shady afternoon climbing behind that rock.

attributes.title: Kalymnos Area
attributes.caption: There are probably around a thousand climbs in this photo alone.

attributes.title: Behind the Olive Press
attributes.caption: This is a first person photo of a really fun section on a 6c+ that I enjoyed. Well bolted, pumpy, lie-back to face transition.

attributes.title: Kalymnos Castle
attributes.caption: We had no idea we were going to be climbing across the valley from an ancient castle!

attributes.title: How Greek is This
attributes.caption: So Greek.

attributes.title: Jack getting ready to pull a roof
attributes.caption: The following roof move gives you a full leg heel hook for a clipping stance, much appreciated.

attributes.title: Secret Garden from the Left
attributes.caption: The crag from one side. What a glorious piece of limestone.

attributes.title: Standing on a Tufa
attributes.caption: This is on Frapogalo 6c. The crux is at the beginning, and then you get to stand on a tufa blob for a rest.

attributes.title: Jack on Ricounet 7a
attributes.caption: I was at a rest in a cave and managed to snap a few cool shots of Jack.

attributes.title: Starting Ballos 7a+
attributes.caption: Oops, almost clipped, try again.

attributes.title: Cory on Ballos 7a+
attributes.caption: Me, sunburnt, and working hard. I didn't make it to the top on this one, but had a few good burns on it.

attributes.title: Steph Seeks Tufa
attributes.caption: Steph on her way to tufa-town.

attributes.title: Secret Garden from the Right
attributes.caption: Another crag overview shot. Just as we were leaving we spotted a pod of dolphins which would probably be in frame in the ocean, but they can't be seen here.

attributes.title: Telendos Sunset
attributes.caption: Yet another glorious sunset, looking out at the island of Telendos.

attributes.title: Telendos at Dawn
attributes.caption: After being awoken uncerimoniously by a mosquito, I wandered outside and snapped this picture.

attributes.title: More Goats
attributes.caption: They're always there, and they love apple cores. So nice to not have to pack those out.

attributes.title: Cory Climbing
attributes.caption: Getting some!

attributes.title: View from Telendos
attributes.caption: At the top of our big climb.

attributes.title: Ried
attributes.caption: Yay! No more climbing shoes!

attributes.title: Ried in the Rubble
attributes.caption: This is just near a tiny church on the hill.

attributes.title: Inside the Site
attributes.caption: Candle is still burning, not quite sure what the significance is, but I'm fairly certain it's Jesus related.

attributes.title: Pilgramage Site
attributes.caption: I was told people come here to pray and light candles.

attributes.title: Walk off Telendos
attributes.caption: As the decent goes on, the hike eventually winds past a nude beach and ends at a bar. Not bad.

attributes.title: New hat selfie
attributes.caption: Digging my new hat.

attributes.title: Rappelling off of Grande Grotto
attributes.caption: I'm told it requires two 80m ropes. I believe it.
